Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[FMD is endemic in Zambia. The following information is available from the WRLFMD-Pirbright Institute web site at http://www.wrlfmd.org/southern-africa/zambia#panel-6551.

FMDV serotype / Years (not comprehensive)
Untyped / 1932-1933
O / 1976, 1982, 2000, 2010, 2018
A / 1990, 2015
SAT 1 / Livestock: 1953-1955, 1973-1974, 1979-1981, 1987-1988, 2000, 2004-2005, 2008-2009, 2012. Buffalo: 1993, 1996
SAT 2/ Livestock: 1948, 1950, 1956-1958, 1960, 1964-1965, 1969, 1975, 1981-1982, 2007-2009, 2012, 2015. Buffalo: 1993, 1996
SAT 3 / Livestock: 2015, 2017. Buffalo: 1974, 1993, 1996

Note: All three SAT serotypes are probably endemic in the African buffalo (_Syncerus caffer_) population.

FMD virus strain serotype A, topotype AFRICA, lineage G-1 was identified in Mupata village, Mpulungu district, Northern province in 2015. See genotyping report at http://www.wrlfmd.org/sites/world/files/quick_media/WRLFMD-2016-00022-ZAM-GTR-O-A_001.pdf.

The serotyping result to the current event can be seen at http://www.wrlfmd.org/sites/world/files/quick_media/WRLFMD-2018-00032-ZAM-DSR-O-A_001.pdf. The genotyping report is not available yet, http://www.wrlfmd.org/southern-africa/zambia#panel-6552. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED map available at:
Northern Province, Northern, Zambia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6285793,2938]
